This dataset contains loan application records used to predict whether a borrower will fully repay a loan.
It includes 9,578 entries and 14 features such as credit policy status, loan purpose, interest rate, installment amount, annual income, 
debt-to-income ratio, FICO score, credit line history, revolving balance, and public records. The target variable is not.fully.paid, which indicates 
if the loan was not completely repaid. This dataset is commonly used for machine learning classification tasks such as Decision 
  Trees and Random Forest models to analyze borrower risk.
